structuredData.description: Semrush - online visibility management and content marketing SaaS platform

acceptedAnswer.text: A Local Directory Listing, also called a Local Listing, or a Business Listing, is a short online profile containing essential information about your business, such as your business name, address, phone number, website, and other important contact information.

mainEntity.name: What is a local directory listing?

acceptedAnswer.text: Maintaining up-to-date business listings helps your customers to find and contact you more easily. Accurate business listings across multiple directories can also help to improve your local SEO by helping Google to deliver correct contact information when your customers search for you.

Local Listing Management is the process of checking and updating your business information, such as your business name, phone number, address, or website, in all the online directories where that information is published.

Semrush’s Listing Management Tool makes this process easier by enabling you to edit your information using Semrush, and automatically distribute your updates to top local directories in the United States and around the world.

Listing Management is a set-up-and-go tool. Once you set up your location - the information will update across all directories automatically and save your time.

Once you have added either a Basic or Premium location to your Semrush account, the next step is to set it up. If your business is already listed in some directories, you can enter your company name to update your listings immediately. If you have not yet set up any business listings, you can create one by providing the following information about your business:

  • Country
  • Business Name
  • Address
  • Phone Number
  • Postal Code.

As soon as you set it - you can distribute it directly to directories. If you wish you can add any additional info any time. Find out more about setting up a new location here.

mainEntity.name: How do I start using the Listing Management tool?

acceptedAnswer.text: The Listing Management Tool empowers businesses by distributing information to over 150 globally supported directories across 60+ countries. Unlock a world of opportunities for your business. To explore a complete list of countries and directories covered by Listing Management, click here.

mainEntity.name: Which directories does Semrush Listing Management distribute to?

acceptedAnswer.text:
• An Essentials location costs $50 per month per location.
  • An Advanced location costs $60 per month per location.

Learn more about our pricing.

mainEntity.name: How much does the subscription cost?

acceptedAnswer.text:
You can cancel your subscription any time - just reach out to us at or cancel it in your account.

When you cancel your subscription, your local business listings will no longer be distributed.
